# AI-Powered HR Policy Assistant (KnowledgeBot)

The HR Policy Assistant is an AI-powered chatbot that helps employees quickly find answers to company policies such as leave, remote work, benefits, reimbursements, and more.

It combines:

Java (Gradle project) → Initial prototype 

FastAPI (Python) → Backend REST API (to expose /ask endpoint)

Streamlit (Python) → Web UI (chat-like interface for users)

Policies JSON → Knowledge base for responses

🚀 Features

✅ Ask questions about HR policies in natural language

✅ Knowledge base stored in a single policies.json file

✅ Clean and intuitive web UI (Streamlit)

✅ REST API (/ask endpoint via FastAPI)

✅ Predefined examples to guide users

✅ Categories sidebar for better navigation

Ask questions about HR policies in natural language

Clean and intuitive web UI (built with Streamlit)

REST API (/ask endpoint) for programmatic access

Policies loaded from policies.json (easy to update)

Example categories: Leave, Remote Work, Health Insurance, Salary, Performance Reviews

🛠️ Setup Instructions
1. Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/mohsinjaved1165/knowledgebot.git
cd knowledgebot

2. Create & Activate Virtual Environment
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # Mac/Linux
venv\Scripts\activate      # Windows

3. Install Dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

▶️ Running the Project
1. Start FastAPI Backend
uvicorn api:app --reload


Runs at: http://localhost:8000

Endpoint:

curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/ask \
     -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
     -d '{"question": "What is the leave policy?", "userId": "demo"}'

2. Start Streamlit Frontend
streamlit run ui.py


Runs at: http://localhost:8501

💡 Example Questions

"Tell me about leave policy?"

"What is the maternity leave policy?"

"What’s the remote work policy?"

"Tell me about working hours?"

📂 Project Structure
knowledgebot/
│── api.py              # FastAPI backend
│── ui.py               # Streamlit frontend
│── policies.json       # Knowledge base
│── requirements.txt    # Python dependencies
│── README.md           # Documentation

📝 Notes

Update policies.json to add/change company policies.

Backend + UI communicate via http://localhost:8000/ask.

Easily deployable to Heroku, Vercel, or Docker for production.
